      <section eId="sec_7_6_15">
        <num>7-6.15</num>
        <heading>Custodian's expenses, compensation, and bond</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_6_15__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A custodian is entitled to reimbursement from custodial property\nfor reasonable expenses incurred in the performance of the custodian's\nduties.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_6_15__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except for one who is a transferor under 7-6.4, a custodian has an\nelection during each calendar year to charge reasonable compensation for\nservices performed during that year. A custodian's election to charge\nreasonable compensation for a calendar year must be exercised during the\ncalendar year.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_6_15__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as provided in paragraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_6_15__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of 7-6.18, a custodian shall\nnot be required to give a bond.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
